The paper discusses the use of molecular spin valves as synapses in neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural networks and learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of magnetoresistance, which is a phenomenon related to electromagnetism (cs.ET) and the alignment of magnetizations, which is related to electromagnetism and materials science (cs.EM, cs.MS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of voltage pulses to modify the conductance of the molecular spin valves, which is related to nanoelectronics (cs.NANO).
